:\"**Researching usage documentation**\\n\\nI need to explore the normal usage of certain documents. To get started, querying the GitHub README could be a logical step since it's a common place to find helpful information. I'll check for any guidelines or best practices mentioned there that might clarify usage. This will help me ensure I'm on the right track and using the resources correctly. Let's see what I can find!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NRcKDbIAsFBrMY4GxcdOnMA8|fc_02d9bcdad1129063016a407b8089c48193bd393a67ee483fe7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurls = [\n 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/master/README.md',\n 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/v5.0.0/jsonschema-module-swagger-2/README.md',\n 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/v5.0.0/README.md'\n]\nfor url in urls:\n    print('\\n---', url, '---')\n    try:\n        data=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).read().decode()\n        for line in data.splitlines():\n            if any(s.lower() in line.lower() for s in ['swagger', 'jsonschema-module-swagger-2', 'swagger2module', 'jackson']):\n                print(line[:220])\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(type(e).__name__, e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2241, "output": 1262, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22447, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782610793965, "responseId": "resp_02d9bcdad1129063016a407b6a5f448193b96199425cba7bfa"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_NRcKDbIAsFBrMY4GxcdOnMA8|fc_02d9bcdad1129063016a407b8089c48193bd393a67ee483fe7", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\n--- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/master