*\\n\\nI'm looking at the action for advisory_preparation, and I wonder if I need to include \\\"tools.jackson.core:jackson-databind:3.0.3.\\\" Since the test code may use JsonNode and the generator pulls it as a compile dependency, it seems relevant. But if the normal scaffold has a tested module and we add the generator, it includes tools.jackson transitively. Still, there's a compile error with \\\"JsonNode cannot find,\\\" which makes me think the import might be missing. It looks like Jackson 3's relocation is causing the trouble. I need to figure out how to resolve this incompatibility between tools.jackson and com.fasterxml.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Dependencies**\\n\\nI'm finding that the existing error isn't due to incompatible types; it's actually just a missing symbol from com.fasterxml. If I include com.fasterxml.jackson.databind, it would likely show incompatible types instead. So that's a no-go. Instead, I think I should include a deterministic dependency like swagger-annotations with version 2.2.41 instead of 2.2.25, since the existing one is hardcoded and might cause issues. The driver can specifically apply the required version as needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_WkKNPJ70ZKywkNJDannP7tqQ|fc_02d9bcdad1129063016a407b976110819382b4d67f8ea6b7be", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re, xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nfor artifact in ['swagger-annotations']:\n    url=f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/swagger/core/v3/{artifact}/2.2.41/{artifact}-2.2.41.pom'\n    print(url)\n    print(urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).status)\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 982, "output": 955, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24977, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782610821200, "responseId": "